Table A: Running EQ6 from EQ3/6-V8.0a (R43a) for PC
Description= 'Calcite saturated NaCl brine; PHRQPITZ test problem 5b'
This is part of the EQ3/6 Test Case Library
Add halite (NaCl) to the calcite saturated fresh water defined in the
EQ3NR test case input file calnacl.3i; until halite saturation is reached.
Saturation with calcite is maintained by adding calcite as a reactant.
Because the solution is initially saturated; the calcite reactant is almost
immediately converted to product mineral status; regardless of the value of
specified relative rate of dissolution. The log pCO2 is fixed at -2.0 by
means of an nffg option. This is test problem 5b from the PHRQPITZ manual
(Plummer et al.; 1988). This problem has no redox aspect.
